Welp, The first 12 days of 2023 have been BULLSHIT!! Today I walked into the hospital and into my appointment that was only supposed to be a simple 5min in-clinic procedure… ended up being there from 8a-4p. Procedure gone wrong, horrific pain, foot is numb, ankle won’t move, I couldn’t walk… I left out of there in a wheelchair, with crutches in hand and a boot on!! I cussed and cried all day. The thought of another surgery (I’ve had 4 already) and the thought of being in that boot again (I was in it for 2 straight years 3 yrs ago) was not sitting right with me. 🙄🤦🏾‍♀️ #overit

⚠️Transparent moment⚠️
**Long Post**
When I say, God definitely has me on his warriors list… believe that!
July 21, 2023 While in the mirror, describing to my Man how I want my breasts to sit if I ever got a boob job, I found a lump in my breast! 😰 after him confirming what I felt, It put me in a panic. I reached out to my doctor and scheduled an appointment and mammogram to put my mind at ease. Unfortunately, An inconclusive mammogram led to an abnormal ultrasound which led to a referral for a biopsy. After complaining for 3wks about delayed results, I looked in the portal and there it was, posted a week prior, I had been diagnosed with Stage 2, Grade 3 Breast Cancer. 🤦🏾‍♀️🤯 Since then (2wks) I’ve met with My Oncologist, my Oncology Surgeon, and my Plastic surgeon. My Oncologist informed me that the mass has tripled in size since the biopsy and now has me scheduled for a double mastectomy in the next week. 🤯🤯 As strong as I think I am, I feel so weak and defeated right now. I’m overwhelmed and I feel broken. I’m an emotional wreck! And As much as I try to save face and cry behind closed doors, IM HURT! I initially had to tell my partner through text msgs since he’s away training😭 and it’s killing me cause he is my safe place. I had to tell my children about this because everything is happening so fast and I’m trying to prepare them and now they’re dealing with the hurt as well. I’ve been going about my days as if this isn’t happening when in reality IT DEFINITELY IS. I guess all of these emotions comes with the territory. I know it won’t do me any good to stay in this emotional state for too long but trying to power through 24/7 is exhausting and  unrealistic… I’m tired already. My emotions are valid tho, right?. Smh, I just wanna feel whatever I need to feel w/o judgement… but my children are watching and they don’t even know a “weak me”! 😩
So, here’s to this journey I’m about to embark on, this fight I’m about to fight, and this life I’m about to live! 
Always thankful for your love, prayers, and support from afar💕

Tomorrow I undergo my double mastectomy surgery as the start of my Breast Cancer Journey. Wear pink with me and pray for me💕
